Sentencas: Dynamic behavior of the segmented-in-series tubular solid oxide fuel cell upon discharge was investigated.
Titulo: Dynamic Behavior of Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell upon Discharge

Sentencas: The cell performance decreased initially at 900 degrees C, accompanied by the increase of ohmic resistance.
Titulo: Dynamic Behavior of Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell upon Discharge

Sentencas: Lower partial pressure of oxygen in the cathode resulted in a more severe decrease, whereas the gas displacement in the anode compartment did not induce such behavior.
Titulo: Dynamic Behavior of Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell upon Discharge

Sentencas: As the current was cut off, the ohmic resistance rapidly recovered toward the starting value before current load.
Titulo: Dynamic Behavior of Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell upon Discharge

Sentencas: The possible origin for this increase-recovery behavior of the ohmic resistance has been discussed based on the evaluation of oxygen partial pressure at the cathode/electrolyte interface and element interdiffusion between cathode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Dynamic Behavior of Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell upon Discharge
